de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.winter.matching.blockers

Class AbstractBlocker<RecordType extends Matchable,BlockedType extends Matchable,CorrespondenceType extends Matchable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.winter.matching.blockers.AbstractBlocker<RecordType,BlockedType,CorrespondenceType>
  • Type Parameters:
    RecordType - The type of Records in the input dataset(s)
    BlockedType - The type of Records in the Correspondences (Pairs) that are the result of the blocking
    CorrespondenceType - The type of Records in the causes of the Correspondences (Pairs) that are the result of the blocking
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BlockingKeyIndexer, CorrespondenceCombiningBlocker, GoldStandardBlocker, SortedNeighbourhoodBlocker, StandardBlocker, StandardBlockerWithBlockFiltering, ValueBasedBlocker

    public abstract class AbstractBlocker<RecordType extends Matchable,BlockedType extends Matchable,CorrespondenceType extends Matchable>
extends Object
    The super class for all blocking strategies. The generation of pairs based on the AbstractBlocker can be executed for one dataset, by implementing SymmetricBlocker or for two datasets, by implementing Blocker resolution.
    Author:
    Oliver Lehmberg (oli@dwslab.de), Robert Meusel (robert@dwslab.de)
